✅ Key Idea

A binary heap stored in an array where parent ≥ children.
Parent at i → left child 2*i, right child 2*i+1.
Max-heap property: every parent ≥ its children.

Operations:

push(val): Insert new value → bubble it up until parent is larger.
pop(): Remove root (largest) → move last element to root → percolate down.
heapify(arr): Build heap in O(n) by percolating down from last parent.

