"Max-heap → array-based tree where parent ≥ children. Push = bubble up. Pop = percolate down."

⚡ Full Approach

Heap Representation
Use an array with a dummy -inf at index 0 to simplify math.
Real elements start at index 1.

Push (Insert)
Append new value at the end.
Bubble up while parent < child.

Pop (Extract Max)
Save root (max).
Move last element to root.
Percolate down: swap with larger child until heap property is restored.

Heapify (Build Heap)
Start from last parent → percolate down each node.
Runs in O(n).

Peek
Return root (max) without removing.

Helper: _percolate_down(idx)
While left child exists:
Pick larger of left/right child.
If child > current, swap and continue.
Else stop (heap property satisfied).

➡️ This ensures insertions and deletions maintain O(log n) time complexity.

⏱️ Complexity

